Vendored subset of the fast_float C++ library, used by Python/pystrtod.c
for string-to-float conversion (replaces _Py_dg_strtod from the old
Python/dtoa.c).

Upstream:    https://github.com/fastfloat/fast_float
Version:     v8.0.0 (commit 77cc847)
License:     Apache-2.0 OR MIT OR BSL-1.0 (triple; see LICENSE-* files)

Files included (all 9 upstream headers; fast_float is header-only and
#include'ing `fast_float.h` transitively pulls in the rest):

    fast_float.h              — umbrella header, sole entry point for users
    parse_number.h            — dispatch into the parser pipeline
    float_common.h            — IEEE 754 bit layout, limits, adjusted_mantissa
    ascii_number.h            — fast byte-level digit parsing
    decimal_to_binary.h       — Clinger fast-path + Eisel-Lemire 64-bit path
    digit_comparison.h        — big-int fallback for hard halfway cases
    bigint.h                  — 4000-bit fixed-capacity bigint backing the
                                fallback
    fast_table.h              — precomputed power-of-10 table
    constexpr_feature_detect.h — compiler-probe macros
    LICENSE-APACHE, LICENSE-MIT, LICENSE-BOOST

Algorithm: Clinger's "small value" fast path → Eisel-Lemire 64-bit → if
indeterminate, digit-comparison bignum. This is the same two-phase
design used by Rust std, Go's strconv, DuckDB, Apache Arrow, folly, etc.
Correctness is known-good for every halfway case a double can express,
including the wuffs-HPD failure mode documented in test_strtod.

Integration: Python/_fast_float/fast_float_strtod.cc wraps
`fast_float::from_chars` behind a C ABI entry point
_Py_fast_float_strtod that mirrors the old _Py_dg_strtod calling
convention (ASCII C string in, double out, *endptr points past the
consumed portion, errno = ERANGE on over/underflow).

Build configuration:

    $(CXX) -std=c++17 -fno-exceptions -fno-rtti

fast_float is header-only; the only .cc file in this directory is our
own shim. No throw sites in the hot path when -fno-exceptions is set —
parse errors are returned via `std::errc`.

Updating:

    git clone --branch vX.Y.Z --depth 1 https://github.com/fastfloat/fast_float.git
    cp fast_float/include/fast_float/*.h Python/_fast_float/
    cp fast_float/LICENSE-* Python/_fast_float/

Then update this file's version and commit hash.
